text: Welcome. I'm David. I appreciate you taking this step. What brings you here today?
I've been really overwhelmed with work and home life. I feel like I'm dropping balls everywhere and I don't know how to manage it all.
That sounds exhausting. Many people feel this way when they're trying to do too much. Let's start by getting clear on your priorities. Can you list your top 3 responsibilities right now?
Work deadlines, taking care of my kids, and keeping the house clean.
Good awareness. Now, let's think about the 80/20 rule - 80% of your results come from 20% of your efforts. Which of these three gives you the most return on your energy investment?
Probably work - that's what pays the bills. But I feel guilty when I neglect the kids or the house.

That guilt is common but unhelpful. Let's reframe this: 'Good enough' is good enough for most things. Your kids need your presence more than a perfectly clean house. What would happen if you lowered your standards on cleaning by 20%?
I'd have more time for the kids and myself. That actually sounds doable.

Excellent insight. Let's build a simple time-blocking system. Try this: 7-9 AM work focus, 5-7 PM family time, and protect one hour daily for yourself. What time would work best for your personal hour?
Maybe 8-9 PM after the kids are in bed.
Perfect. Start there. Small changes compound into big results. Track how you feel at the end of the week and we'll adjust from there.
